1
00:00:26,520 --> 00:00:28,520
You are happy, aren't you?

2
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:33,120
Your eyes are closed, so how can you know that?

3
00:00:39,160 --> 00:00:44,120
Your happiness is so strong I can almost feel it.

4
00:00:45,480 --> 00:00:47,080
What a good girl you are.

5
00:00:49,360 --> 00:00:51,040
The same as you,

6
00:00:51,520 --> 00:00:53,360
who are good at everything.

7
00:00:55,080 --> 00:00:57,200
Since when do you talk like this?

8
00:00:59,520 --> 00:01:01,520
Like what?

9
00:01:01,680 --> 00:01:03,160
This isn't strange.

10
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:05,920
It feels strange because you have such a naughty mind.

11
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:10,200
But it really isn't strange, you know?

12
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:13,720
It's normal for people who are about to get married.

13
00:01:14,760 --> 00:01:16,200
Really?

14
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:18,400
You naughty girl.

15
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:23,640
I have something for you.

16
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:25,040
Hm?

17
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:45,400
Actually, I meant to give it to you last night.

18
00:01:46,600 --> 00:01:48,280
But I just couldn't find the right moment.

19
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:52,320
Turn around, I'll put it on for you.

20
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:24,240
Do you like it?

21
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:27,960
Of course, I do.

22
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:32,640
Thank you.

23
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:41,760
Will I really get to wake up to the sight of you every morning?

24
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:44,200
I'm so excited.

25
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:46,560
Since I met you,

26
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:49,000
everything feels exciting.

27
00:02:58,520 --> 00:02:59,840
So, do you like it?

28
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:03,560
Yes, I do.

29
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:13,360
Morning.

30
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:28,960
How's it going?

31
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,960
Have you found any clues?

32
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,400
As before, ma'am,

33
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:37,160
I only found people who looked alike.

34
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,520
When I asked them,

35
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:41,280
the details didn't match yours.

36
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:47,120
Then keep looking.

37
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:51,560
I believe they're still alive.

38
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:56,080
But ma'am...

39
00:04:58,280 --> 00:05:00,280
It's been a long time.

40
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:04,600
You shouldn't get your hopes up.

41
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:10,560
I'm not giving up hope.

42
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:15,440
Keep doing your job.

43
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:25,960
I hope to see them again

44
00:05:28,280 --> 00:05:29,720
while I'm still alive.

45
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:32,960
I'll try my best, ma'am.

46
00:05:46,960 --> 00:05:47,960
Thank you.

47
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:51,400
Wow...

48
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:54,200
It's just a pre-wedding shoot. Do you have to look this beautiful?

49
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:57,040
It's the bride's glow.

50
00:05:57,080 --> 00:06:00,040
Did you just realize how beautiful your girlfriend is?

51
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,880
Perfect timing. Okay, come on!

52
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:05,360
Keep going. Pose! Three, two...

53
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:08,360
That's good. Three, two...

54
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:09,720
Good.

55
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:11,760
Three, two...

56
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:18,560
Still can't decide?

57
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:21,280
I can't make up my mind.

58
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,040
They're all beautiful.

59
00:07:23,320 --> 00:07:25,880
How can I pick the right one for my artwork?

60
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:30,080
Just pick the one you like.

61
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:31,680
I trust your taste.

62
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:33,440
Okay.

63
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:36,320
Then I'll pick the one where we both look beautiful,

64
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,720
for fairness.

65
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:39,760
I look beautiful in all of them.

66
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:41,160
Hmm...

67
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,400
Not gonna argue with that.

68
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,240
This one is cute.

69
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:53,080
You look so happy.

70
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:57,080
Of course, I do.

71
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:00,520
We're really getting married.

72
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:04,360
And our life as a couple is different from everyone else's.

73
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:06,680
It was quite a rough patch to get through.

74
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:08,120
We also have my mom to deal with.

75
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,360
It's like we're in a movie.

76
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:11,720
Well...

77
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:15,640
I think our life as a couple is even more dramatic than a movie plot.

78
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:17,840
But your mother plays the villain.

79
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:19,480
Hey!

80
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,120
But it's true.

81
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:25,880
Anyway, it's a happy ending

82
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:29,280
because the main characters got married.

83
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:32,320
After this, we'll be happy with nothing standing in our way.

84
00:08:32,920 --> 00:08:34,240
Right?

85
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:35,280
Right?!

86
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:37,120
Right. That's right.

87
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,160
Beautiful, right?

88
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,680
What are you doing?

89
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:31,080
Don't you want a gift before the big day?

90
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,920
Why are you wearing a sexy dress?

91
00:10:14,880 --> 00:10:16,400
Hey!

92
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:21,120
I'm trying to be sexy.

93
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:23,280
Why are you laughing?

94
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:25,000
I'm sorry. Can you do it again?

95
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,600
No, I'm not gonna.

96
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:34,320
You don't have to wear a sexy dress.

97
00:10:36,040 --> 00:10:37,840
You've already won my heart.

98
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,280
What about you?

99
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:47,120
What were you thinking about?

100
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:48,240
Afraid of something?

101
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:52,840
No, I'm not.

102
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,840
There's nothing to be afraid of.

103
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:04,000
The only thing I'm afraid of...

104
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:07,680
What's that?

105
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:12,920
I'm afraid that one day you won't love me anymore.

106
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:22,760
Then you don't have to worry about it

107
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:29,440
because I'll never ever leave you.

108
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:32,040
Really?

109
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:33,840
Of course!

110
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:39,320
I'm so happy

111
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:41,840
that we're going to live together.

112
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:13,080
Me too.

113
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:20,040
Am I sexy?

114
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:21,560
Please don't try.

115
00:13:21,453 --> 00:13:23,853
Hello!

116
00:13:26,213 --> 00:13:28,173
Hello, ladies and gentlemen

117
00:13:28,213 --> 00:13:32,653
who have gathered here to celebrate the wedding of Arisa and Lalin.

118
00:13:32,693 --> 00:13:35,693
Brides, please show yourself.

119
00:15:05,093 --> 00:15:07,453
Coming up, we have a special moment

120
00:15:07,493 --> 00:15:10,893
for the two brides to say their vows

121
00:15:11,053 --> 00:15:13,933
before the guests, family, and friends.

122
00:15:24,413 --> 00:15:25,413
Lalin,

123
00:15:27,653 --> 00:15:30,013
your name means the moon,

124
00:15:31,933 --> 00:15:34,893
shining in the night

125
00:15:35,693 --> 00:15:37,453
or when darkness consumes.

126
00:15:41,613 --> 00:15:43,413
Before I met you,

127
00:15:45,013 --> 00:15:46,533
my life...

128
00:15:47,093 --> 00:15:48,573
was once engulfed in darkness.

129
00:15:50,693 --> 00:15:52,613
But ever since we crossed paths,

130
00:15:53,653 --> 00:15:56,013
there was never a glimpse of darkness again.

131
00:16:01,013 --> 00:16:02,293
I promise

132
00:16:02,733 --> 00:16:05,213
I will treasure this light

133
00:16:08,133 --> 00:16:10,093
for as long as I shall live.

134
00:16:16,693 --> 00:16:18,413
I love you, Lalin.

135
00:16:31,493 --> 00:16:33,773
I want to thank you, Arisa.

136
00:16:34,693 --> 00:16:37,373
I've been thankful since the day we first met.

137
00:16:40,293 --> 00:16:43,773
You've changed my views on so many things and...

138
00:16:44,213 --> 00:16:45,693
made me understand myself a lot more.

139
00:16:47,973 --> 00:16:49,973
I wish to be with you for so long,

140
00:16:50,213 --> 00:16:51,533
for eternity,

141
00:16:52,853 --> 00:16:55,213
because every second I share with you

142
00:16:57,093 --> 00:16:59,093
has made me so happy.

143
00:17:01,653 --> 00:17:03,093
I love you, too.

144
00:17:08,773 --> 00:17:10,933
You can now exchange rings.

145
00:18:04,813 --> 00:18:06,573
Kiss! Kiss!

146
00:18:06,613 --> 00:18:08,093
Kiss! Kiss!

147
00:18:08,093 --> 00:18:09,853
Kiss! Kiss!

148
00:18:09,853 --> 00:18:11,613
Kiss! Kiss!

149
00:18:11,693 --> 00:18:13,653
Kiss! Kiss!

150
00:18:13,653 --> 00:18:16,253
Kiss! Kiss! Kiss!

151
00:18:16,253 --> 00:18:20,333
Kiss! Kiss!

152
00:18:30,933 --> 00:18:34,093
Alright, it's now the much-awaited moment,

153
00:18:34,133 --> 00:18:35,933
the most romantic time of all.

154
00:18:35,973 --> 00:18:38,533
Please loudly cheer for both the brides

155
00:18:38,573 --> 00:18:41,013
for their first dance!

156
00:19:44,613 --> 00:19:45,893
What a nice facade.

157
00:19:48,973 --> 00:19:50,853
No matter what, I still don't trust that woman.

158
00:19:53,613 --> 00:19:55,093
Keep an eye on her.

159
00:20:02,253 --> 00:20:03,653
I will try, ma'am.

160
00:20:29,533 --> 00:20:30,253
Hey!

161
00:20:30,373 --> 00:20:31,573
Hey, hey!

162
00:20:31,573 --> 00:20:32,573
Step back!

163
00:20:36,173 --> 00:20:37,933
Are you alright? Put that down first.

164
00:20:41,493 --> 00:20:43,093
Did you get splashed by the oil?

165
00:20:44,093 --> 00:20:45,453
I'm okay.

166
00:20:46,933 --> 00:20:49,773
You're acting like I'm a child.

167
00:20:51,373 --> 00:20:53,573
So where is the maid? Why are you doing this yourself?

168
00:20:55,213 --> 00:20:57,213
I asked her to do something else.

169
00:20:59,453 --> 00:21:01,333
I want to show off my cooking.

170
00:21:01,613 --> 00:21:05,213
I want a cute moment where I make a meal for my girlfriend to bring to work.

171
00:21:08,773 --> 00:21:10,013
Dear...

172
00:21:11,453 --> 00:21:13,653
You don't have to pamper me all that much.

173
00:21:17,893 --> 00:21:20,573
You have my whole heart, so what else could you possibly need?

174
00:21:21,973 --> 00:21:23,893
No one's a master at everything.

175
00:21:25,893 --> 00:21:28,973
Jeez, it's just cooking.

176
00:21:29,253 --> 00:21:30,653
Easy peasy.

177
00:21:30,733 --> 00:21:33,053
The taste is beside the point, right?

178
00:21:33,453 --> 00:21:34,813
Are you gonna eat it or not?

179
00:21:35,133 --> 00:21:36,453
Of course, I am.

180
00:21:40,533 --> 00:21:42,133
- Right, - Hm?

181
00:21:42,573 --> 00:21:45,013
I've found the destination for our honeymoon.

182
00:21:47,733 --> 00:21:49,333
I wanna go to Paris.

183
00:21:49,453 --> 00:21:51,533
City of Love.

184
00:21:52,293 --> 00:21:53,813
It just seems so romantic.

185
00:21:53,813 --> 00:21:55,333
I've always wanted to go.

186
00:21:55,333 --> 00:21:57,973
How about we wear matching outfits

187
00:21:57,973 --> 00:22:00,173
and take some photos in front of the Eiffel Tower?

188
00:22:00,813 --> 00:22:02,973
Sounds cute, doesn't it? What do you say?

189
00:22:04,053 --> 00:22:04,973
Anything is great.

190
00:22:05,693 --> 00:22:08,013
Whatever you like, I'll let you have it your way.

191
00:22:10,293 --> 00:22:11,453
Then...

192
00:22:12,213 --> 00:22:13,653
I'll catch up on work quickly.

193
00:22:14,253 --> 00:22:15,533
How about we take that trip next month?

194
00:22:16,293 --> 00:22:17,253
Sounds great.

195
00:22:18,493 --> 00:22:20,253
But I'm not gonna let you cook anymore.

196
00:22:20,373 --> 00:22:22,773
What? Why? I want you to eat my food.

197
00:22:22,933 --> 00:22:24,493
How about I eat something else first?

198
00:22:24,973 --> 00:22:26,333
What do you say? Hm?

199
00:22:28,293 --> 00:22:30,013
Oh, give me just a second.

200
00:22:33,253 --> 00:22:35,613
[Ms. Ruwajee]

201
00:22:41,293 --> 00:22:42,373
Hello.

202
00:22:49,573 --> 00:22:50,733
See you.

203
00:23:34,013 --> 00:23:35,173
What is going on?

204
00:23:35,533 --> 00:23:36,733
Why did you call everyone for a meeting?

205
00:23:38,733 --> 00:23:39,853
I have no clue.

206
00:23:40,613 --> 00:23:41,933
All I heard is it's important.

207
00:24:08,973 --> 00:24:12,413
My apologies for such short notice about the meeting.

208
00:24:13,653 --> 00:24:14,573
It's all good.

209
00:24:15,573 --> 00:24:17,293
It's only once in a blue moon that you visit the company.

210
00:24:17,893 --> 00:24:19,133
Should we get into it?

211
00:24:23,533 --> 00:24:25,013
It's nothing major.

212
00:24:25,253 --> 00:24:27,773
It's merely about the shareholders.

213
00:24:30,173 --> 00:24:32,333
I trust that everyone knows

214
00:24:33,093 --> 00:24:36,173
how I barely meddle with the company.

215
00:24:36,813 --> 00:24:40,893
For the past 20 years, I've only been receiving dividends.

216
00:24:42,213 --> 00:24:43,373
As of today,

217
00:24:44,853 --> 00:24:46,893
I don't need them anymore.

218
00:24:49,213 --> 00:24:53,013
I would like to transfer them to the person I trust most.

219
00:24:53,493 --> 00:24:55,253
This share transfer

220
00:24:55,333 --> 00:24:57,653
is in accordance with the company's policy

221
00:24:57,653 --> 00:25:01,813
and has been approved by all the parties concerned.

222
00:25:03,293 --> 00:25:06,573
My 29% share in this company...

223
00:25:07,573 --> 00:25:09,253
I would like to pass it on

224
00:25:13,293 --> 00:25:14,653
to Arisa.

225
00:25:21,493 --> 00:25:23,493
[Share Transfer Agreement]

226
00:25:23,493 --> 00:25:25,053
All my shares...

227
00:25:26,013 --> 00:25:27,253
will be given to you.

228
00:25:27,813 --> 00:25:29,693
Consider this a wedding gift

229
00:25:29,693 --> 00:25:33,533
and a payback for when you gave me money to gamble.

230
00:25:33,773 --> 00:25:35,373
Are you sure, Auntie,

231
00:25:36,213 --> 00:25:37,213
that you'd give them to me?

232
00:25:38,013 --> 00:25:40,973
I trust you with them.

233
00:25:41,813 --> 00:25:43,573
Do whatever you want with them, be my guest.

234
00:25:44,053 --> 00:25:47,133
I'm only asking you to take care of my niece.

235
00:25:56,133 --> 00:25:57,253
Thank you.

236
00:26:00,533 --> 00:26:02,133
Take good care of each other.

237
00:26:13,133 --> 00:26:15,973
Thank you very much for your trust, Ms. Ruwajee.

238
00:26:17,453 --> 00:26:19,733
Since the transfer has been completed,

239
00:26:20,253 --> 00:26:22,893
I would like to move forward to the next session.

240
00:26:30,173 --> 00:26:31,173
What session?

241
00:26:32,613 --> 00:26:35,893
The review on the company's management structure,

242
00:26:36,173 --> 00:26:38,173
including the CEO position.

243
00:26:39,493 --> 00:26:40,693
I was never made aware of that.

244
00:26:41,133 --> 00:26:42,213
What are you talking about?

245
00:26:42,213 --> 00:26:44,493
It's the future of the company.

246
00:26:45,213 --> 00:26:49,453
I have been rightfully granted more shares in accordance with the company's policy,

247
00:26:49,733 --> 00:26:51,933
and the board of directors is well aware of it.

248
00:26:53,133 --> 00:26:54,973
What are you doing, Arisa?

249
00:26:56,773 --> 00:26:58,493
I ask that the board of directors

250
00:26:58,653 --> 00:27:01,573
vote for or against

251
00:27:01,693 --> 00:27:05,213
the dismissal of Ms. Weiling from her position as CEO.

252
00:27:14,653 --> 00:27:17,373
This is proof of false accounting

253
00:27:17,573 --> 00:27:19,173
committed by Ms. Weiling,

254
00:27:19,653 --> 00:27:21,413
which caused the company to fall into the negative.

255
00:27:57,781 --> 00:27:58,661
Hey!

256
00:27:59,421 --> 00:28:01,501
Can you explain what's going on?

257
00:28:02,141 --> 00:28:03,741
Why are you doing this?

258
00:28:14,421 --> 00:28:15,901
You don't need to know.

259
00:28:16,821 --> 00:28:19,701
Knowing your mother deserves this is enough.

260
00:28:20,461 --> 00:28:23,061
Then tell me why you're doing this.

261
00:28:23,501 --> 00:28:24,301
Why?

262
00:28:25,021 --> 00:28:26,301
For your satisfaction?

263
00:28:26,701 --> 00:28:28,901
Or what? You want to get richer?

264
00:28:29,221 --> 00:28:30,941
Do you need more money or something?

265
00:28:31,381 --> 00:28:34,501
You know how much my mom loves this company.

266
00:28:34,501 --> 00:28:36,421
Because your mother loves it,

267
00:28:36,941 --> 00:28:38,261
I have to do this.

268
00:28:40,381 --> 00:28:41,461
I see.

269
00:28:42,581 --> 00:28:44,821
Was all of this your plan?

270
00:28:47,941 --> 00:28:49,461
You made me fall in love with you just to deceive me.

271
00:28:50,621 --> 00:28:52,621
You said you wanted a future with me.

272
00:28:54,181 --> 00:28:57,741
But in the end, that future is only yours. Am I right?

273
00:28:58,741 --> 00:29:00,061
Tell me.

274
00:29:00,581 --> 00:29:03,821
You're only with me because of my mom's company, right?

275
00:29:05,021 --> 00:29:05,901
Right?!

276
00:29:06,541 --> 00:29:07,541
Tell me.

277
00:29:14,021 --> 00:29:14,941
Lalin...

278
00:29:15,901 --> 00:29:16,741
It's...

279
00:29:19,981 --> 00:29:20,981
Lalin...

280
00:29:22,661 --> 00:29:24,861
This is between your mother and me.

281
00:29:24,901 --> 00:29:26,061
It has nothing to do with you.

282
00:29:27,581 --> 00:29:28,941
How can it not concern me?

283
00:29:30,061 --> 00:29:31,981
I'm just a pawn in your game!

284
00:29:32,901 --> 00:29:34,661
I have feelings too, you know.

285
00:29:35,141 --> 00:29:37,941
But all you care about is winning.

286
00:29:45,501 --> 00:29:47,501
One day, you'll understand why I did this.

287
00:29:49,141 --> 00:29:50,781
I don't want to understand anything anymore.

288
00:29:52,501 --> 00:29:55,301
You have no right to destroy my life like this.

289
00:29:56,581 --> 00:29:57,581
Lalin...

290
00:31:15,941 --> 00:31:16,821
Mom...

291
00:31:17,621 --> 00:31:19,341
I'm so sorry.

292
00:31:21,741 --> 00:31:24,701
I didn't think she would dare do this to you.

293
00:31:30,661 --> 00:31:31,901
It's okay, baby.

294
00:31:32,981 --> 00:31:34,781
Don't blame yourself.

295
00:31:40,101 --> 00:31:42,621
How can I not blame myself, Mom?

296
00:31:44,821 --> 00:31:48,741
I was stupid to fall for her.

297
00:31:50,741 --> 00:31:52,421
It's not your fault at all.

298
00:31:54,381 --> 00:31:55,981
Arisa is smart, though.

299
00:31:58,901 --> 00:32:00,741
She knows all of my weaknesses,

300
00:32:02,981 --> 00:32:04,981
from when she stole the Petra Project

301
00:32:06,941 --> 00:32:08,581
to when she sabotaged me

302
00:32:08,941 --> 00:32:10,381
during the loan application,

303
00:32:11,421 --> 00:32:12,981
forcing me to share the allocation with her.

304
00:32:15,101 --> 00:32:17,301
She knows everything about our company.

305
00:32:21,141 --> 00:32:23,301
She intended to hurt me.

306
00:32:27,621 --> 00:32:29,541
She didn't just hurt me;

307
00:32:32,541 --> 00:32:34,341
she also hurt my daughter.

308
00:32:39,221 --> 00:32:40,981
Why did she do all this?

309
00:32:43,421 --> 00:32:45,421
It's not just about the business.

310
00:32:46,901 --> 00:32:48,661
Arisa doesn't need any money.

311
00:32:54,341 --> 00:32:56,461
I don't know either.

312
00:33:02,701 --> 00:33:03,861
Or...

313
00:33:04,661 --> 00:33:07,541
Did you ever have any problems with her in the past?

314
00:33:08,581 --> 00:33:10,461
Have you ever done anything to her?

315
00:33:10,821 --> 00:33:12,741
I didn't know her before.

316
00:33:14,621 --> 00:33:16,861
I had someone look into her background.

317
00:33:17,901 --> 00:33:19,581
There's nothing on her.

318
00:33:21,741 --> 00:33:24,301
If I knew what I had done to her,

319
00:33:25,421 --> 00:33:28,141
I could at least make it up to her.

320
00:33:30,221 --> 00:33:31,741
But I have no idea.

321
00:33:42,341 --> 00:33:43,821
Leave it to me.

322
00:33:45,261 --> 00:33:48,061
I also want to know what Arisa wants.

323
00:33:52,741 --> 00:33:55,501
She's no longer the person I used to know.

324
00:34:23,781 --> 00:34:24,741
Hello.

325
00:34:25,221 --> 00:34:26,901
Sorry to bother you,

326
00:34:27,421 --> 00:34:29,181
but I need your help.

327
00:34:32,101 --> 00:34:33,701
I won't say yes yet.

328
00:34:34,261 --> 00:34:36,261
I'd like to hear your proposal first.

329
00:34:36,821 --> 00:34:39,581
I can give you whatever you want.

330
00:34:40,421 --> 00:34:43,141
I just want you to help me look into Arisa.

331
00:34:45,941 --> 00:34:47,181
Why me?

332
00:34:49,461 --> 00:34:52,101
I know you're a talented reporter.

333
00:34:53,021 --> 00:34:56,101
And now you're looking into my mother, aren't you?

334
00:34:59,341 --> 00:35:00,461
It doesn't matter, though.

335
00:35:02,141 --> 00:35:04,661
I want your help

336
00:35:04,701 --> 00:35:06,501
to find out who Arisa is.

337
00:35:08,861 --> 00:35:11,501
I've also heard you know Ms. Aiy.

338
00:35:11,941 --> 00:35:14,141
That might be one of your clues.

339
00:35:18,701 --> 00:35:20,901
You want me to look into the personal life

340
00:35:20,941 --> 00:35:22,781
of your new spouse?

341
00:35:26,301 --> 00:35:27,061
Yes.

342
00:35:27,941 --> 00:35:29,141
It's funny, isn't it?

343
00:35:30,981 --> 00:35:34,661
That woman came into my life to hurt my mom.

344
00:35:35,301 --> 00:35:37,101
I just want to help her.

345
00:35:41,101 --> 00:35:43,061
I'm sorry to say this,

346
00:35:44,021 --> 00:35:46,781
but your mother isn't really a good person either.

347
00:35:51,021 --> 00:35:52,781
This kind of business...

348
00:35:53,221 --> 00:35:55,301
must have left blood on her hands.

349
00:35:55,501 --> 00:35:56,581
No way.

350
00:35:57,141 --> 00:35:58,461
I know my mom well.

351
00:35:58,501 --> 00:35:59,861
She's never killed anyone.

352
00:36:07,981 --> 00:36:09,261
Before this happened,

353
00:36:09,581 --> 00:36:11,501
what did you know about Arisa?

354
00:36:16,301 --> 00:36:19,221
Arisa rarely told me about her family.

355
00:36:21,301 --> 00:36:24,541
But I know that her parents died in an accident

356
00:36:25,021 --> 00:36:27,101
around 20 years ago.

357
00:36:30,381 --> 00:36:31,861
What are their names?

358
00:36:33,181 --> 00:36:34,861
Thinnakorn and Saitharn.

359
00:36:46,421 --> 00:36:47,541
Hello.

360
00:36:49,101 --> 00:36:50,101
Where is it?

361
00:36:51,661 --> 00:36:53,661
Okay, I'm going now.

362
00:36:55,741 --> 00:36:56,581
Hey.

363
00:36:58,861 --> 00:37:00,581
Where are you going? We're not done talking yet.

364
00:37:00,581 --> 00:37:01,941
I have to go cover the news.

365
00:37:02,621 --> 00:37:04,381
Oh, you should come with me too.

366
00:37:04,741 --> 00:37:05,501
Why?

367
00:37:06,021 --> 00:37:08,581
Your mother is in serious trouble right now.

368
00:37:11,701 --> 00:37:12,781
Hey, wait for me!

369
00:37:13,941 --> 00:37:16,181
You may have seen his face.

370
00:37:16,621 --> 00:37:17,781
Kengkad,

371
00:37:18,141 --> 00:37:20,421
a protester who used to demonstrate outside your building.

372
00:37:21,701 --> 00:37:23,061
I've heard his name before.

373
00:37:23,501 --> 00:37:24,701
But we don't know each other.

374
00:37:24,821 --> 00:37:28,501
He is now in a coma at the hospital after the accident.

375
00:37:29,261 --> 00:37:32,381
The witness testified that on the day of the accident,

376
00:37:33,101 --> 00:37:35,101
your assistant

377
00:37:35,741 --> 00:37:37,981
attempted to bribe him, but he refused.

378
00:37:39,101 --> 00:37:40,541
So, the circumstances of the case

379
00:37:40,581 --> 00:37:42,861
suggest that you

380
00:37:43,341 --> 00:37:45,701
may have prior knowledge of the situation.

381
00:37:46,141 --> 00:37:48,621
I want you to give a truthful statement

382
00:37:48,821 --> 00:37:51,421
because your information can be verified.

383
00:37:52,781 --> 00:37:54,021
As for the bribe,

384
00:37:55,021 --> 00:37:57,021
my lawyers will explain that.

385
00:37:58,021 --> 00:38:00,981
But I can assure you that I didn't do it.

386
00:38:02,061 --> 00:38:03,861
I have never thought of killing anyone,

387
00:38:04,581 --> 00:38:05,861
and I would never do anything underhanded.

388
00:38:09,901 --> 00:38:11,981
Why hasn't she come down yet?

389
00:38:12,021 --> 00:38:13,661
It's been an hour.

390
00:38:15,421 --> 00:38:16,861
- Is that her? - That's her?

391
00:38:16,901 --> 00:38:18,221
- Is that her? Yes, it's her! - Hey! Hey!

392
00:38:18,261 --> 00:38:19,501
Hurry!

393
00:38:19,541 --> 00:38:21,541
Let us interview you for a moment.

394
00:38:21,581 --> 00:38:23,741
Could you explain everything to us?

395
00:38:23,901 --> 00:38:27,421
Is it true that you offered money to the protester?

396
00:38:27,861 --> 00:38:31,141
Was the money you offered related to the recent accident?

397
00:38:31,181 --> 00:38:32,461
Yes, please answer the question.

398
00:38:32,501 --> 00:38:34,861
Is this the same as what happened to Chet,

399
00:38:34,901 --> 00:38:37,541
the protester who died 20 years ago?

400
00:38:37,581 --> 00:38:39,221
- That's right. - Is there any connection?

401
00:38:45,621 --> 00:38:48,461
- Won't you say anything? - Could you show us proof?

402
00:39:11,341 --> 00:39:12,861
We are meeting today

403
00:39:13,861 --> 00:39:15,821
- because I want to talk about… - Get to the point already?

404
00:39:20,141 --> 00:39:21,701
Can I order something first?

405
00:39:21,741 --> 00:39:23,061
I haven't eaten anything yet.

406
00:39:43,701 --> 00:39:45,741
I'll have the Australian sirloin.

407
00:39:45,941 --> 00:39:47,501
Medium rare, please.

408
00:39:48,061 --> 00:39:51,141
Also, spaghetti with dried chilli,

409
00:39:51,781 --> 00:39:53,221
extra spicy.

410
00:39:58,821 --> 00:40:02,301
And a glass of full-bodied red wine, please.

411
00:40:03,781 --> 00:40:04,461
Oh!

412
00:40:05,461 --> 00:40:06,461
Here, Ms. Weiling.

413
00:40:09,781 --> 00:40:11,461
She may not be in the mood to eat.

414
00:40:19,221 --> 00:40:20,541
Honestly,

415
00:40:21,541 --> 00:40:22,741
what do you want?

416
00:40:24,261 --> 00:40:27,061
You're even blaming me for killing people.

417
00:40:27,501 --> 00:40:29,501
Isn't that too much? Huh?

418
00:40:33,461 --> 00:40:35,341
So, you came into Lalin's life…

419
00:40:36,221 --> 00:40:37,341
do you even love her?

420
00:40:38,741 --> 00:40:40,141
Or is everything you've done

421
00:40:40,741 --> 00:40:42,181
just to hurt me?

422
00:40:46,061 --> 00:40:48,461
So you think you're the only one who's been hurt?

423
00:40:51,861 --> 00:40:53,141
Don't you think

424
00:40:53,581 --> 00:40:56,461
you must have hurt someone for things to turn out this badly for you?

425
00:40:57,181 --> 00:40:58,701
I'm not like you,

426
00:41:00,141 --> 00:41:02,461
someone who sacrifices other people's lives to get what they want!

427
00:41:02,501 --> 00:41:03,941
What are you talking about?!

428
00:41:04,901 --> 00:41:06,341
What have I done to you?

429
00:41:06,381 --> 00:41:07,941
Just be straight with me.

430
00:41:07,981 --> 00:41:10,901
If I knew what I did, I could at least make up for it somehow.

431
00:41:11,381 --> 00:41:14,461
Was your subconscious mind broken for a long time or something?

432
00:41:15,621 --> 00:41:17,781
So you've forgotten the bad things you've done.

433
00:41:21,221 --> 00:41:23,821
I guess I need to remind you.

434
00:41:25,021 --> 00:41:27,301
You'll soon realize what you've done.

435
00:41:27,941 --> 00:41:29,941
What you are facing right now

436
00:41:30,181 --> 00:41:32,061
is what you must pay for.

437
00:42:13,990 --> 00:42:16,190
How is it going? Have you been lonely?

438
00:42:17,870 --> 00:42:20,030
It must be lonely always being here in the stall, huh?

439
00:42:20,790 --> 00:42:22,790
I'll take you for a walk today.

440
00:42:34,790 --> 00:42:36,430
But after this...

441
00:42:42,110 --> 00:42:44,630
I won't be visiting as often.

442
00:42:46,390 --> 00:42:48,110
Don't miss me.

443
00:45:51,270 --> 00:45:52,190
Mom.

444
00:45:52,390 --> 00:45:54,630
Why are you still awake? What are you up to?

445
00:45:58,150 --> 00:45:59,590
Just looking through old photos.

446
00:46:05,710 --> 00:46:07,550
I was so young.

447
00:46:07,590 --> 00:46:09,470
I looked so goofy, Mom.

448
00:46:11,750 --> 00:46:13,190
You were adorable.

449
00:46:13,990 --> 00:46:17,270
This was the first time I traveled overseas, wasn't it?

450
00:46:17,350 --> 00:46:19,070
Yes, in Italy.

451
00:46:21,630 --> 00:46:24,310
Speaking of which, I kinda miss Dad.

452
00:46:41,630 --> 00:46:43,470
Who is this person?

453
00:46:48,030 --> 00:46:49,670
She was my best friend in the entire world.

454
00:46:53,790 --> 00:46:55,670
But I haven't seen her in such a long time.

455
00:46:56,950 --> 00:46:58,550
I have no idea how she's been.

456
00:47:02,230 --> 00:47:04,230
I really want to meet her one more time.

457
00:47:06,750 --> 00:47:08,190
What's her name?

458
00:47:08,630 --> 00:47:10,070
She's Saitharn.

459
00:47:13,230 --> 00:47:14,390
Saitharn...

460
00:47:18,030 --> 00:47:19,230
[Mrs. Saitharn Navakul]

461
00:47:25,350 --> 00:47:27,510
Why would you want to meet her again?

462
00:47:28,470 --> 00:47:30,150
Hasn't she already passed away?

463
00:47:32,710 --> 00:47:33,870
What did you find out?

464
00:47:48,590 --> 00:47:50,470
A body was found, identified as Thinnakorn Navakul,

465
00:47:50,510 --> 00:47:51,950
a world-class programmer

466
00:47:51,990 --> 00:47:53,990
in a vacation home. ['Saitharn' might be fatally burned to ashes]

467
00:47:54,230 --> 00:47:56,470
Only his body was found on the scene.

468
00:47:56,470 --> 00:47:58,750
His wife, 'Saitharn Navakul,'

469
00:47:58,790 --> 00:48:01,150
was presumed to be burned to ashes.

470
00:48:10,030 --> 00:48:13,350
But Mom insisted that Auntie Saitharn was still alive.

471
00:48:21,590 --> 00:48:23,670
This is the photo of Mom and Auntie Saitharn

472
00:48:23,910 --> 00:48:25,390
when they were friends.

473
00:48:28,230 --> 00:48:30,230
This news was kept in the archive.

474
00:48:30,270 --> 00:48:31,950
Not a lot of people pay attention to it anymore.

475
00:48:32,870 --> 00:48:35,950
Your mom and Arisa's mom were the closest of friends,

476
00:48:36,510 --> 00:48:38,830
but Saitharn's death...

477
00:48:39,190 --> 00:48:40,790
wasn't real?

478
00:48:41,070 --> 00:48:42,910
Does Arisa even know

479
00:48:42,950 --> 00:48:44,550
that her own mom is still alive?

480
00:48:47,350 --> 00:48:49,470
If Saitharn is genuinely still alive,

481
00:48:50,110 --> 00:48:51,870
we need to find her

482
00:48:53,110 --> 00:48:55,910
before Arisa can get to your mom.

483
00:48:56,470 --> 00:48:57,470
Exactly.

484
00:48:59,270 --> 00:49:01,750
She is the one who knows all of this.

485
00:49:05,590 --> 00:49:06,910
I'll leave you to it.

486
00:49:10,190 --> 00:49:12,230
Are you sure she's still alive?

487
00:49:12,510 --> 00:49:13,550
I am.

488
00:49:14,150 --> 00:49:16,430
No matter what, the quicker we find her, the better.

489
00:49:23,590 --> 00:49:26,110
But this case is 20 years old.

490
00:49:44,190 --> 00:49:45,270
Hello there,

491
00:49:46,070 --> 00:49:47,270
Ms. Keetraphat.

492
00:49:57,630 --> 00:50:00,110
Is there anything you want to tell me, Kee?

493
00:50:05,910 --> 00:50:08,230
I'm asking you, "Is there anything you want to tell me?"

494
00:50:10,550 --> 00:50:12,470
Is there anything you want to tell me?!

495
00:50:19,830 --> 00:50:20,990
Nothing.

496
00:50:25,670 --> 00:50:27,190
In the end,

497
00:50:27,230 --> 00:50:29,910
you're still refusing to tell me the truth, huh?

498
00:50:35,750 --> 00:50:36,950
But it's fine.

499
00:50:38,030 --> 00:50:40,510
I already know everything.

500
00:50:42,950 --> 00:50:46,110
Your plan to destroy my mom is already a success, isn't it?

501
00:50:47,750 --> 00:50:49,310
Congrats.

502
00:50:51,630 --> 00:50:55,270
That would include hurting me in the process.

503
00:50:58,510 --> 00:51:00,510
It must be another gain, right?

504
00:51:06,190 --> 00:51:09,390
I understand how excruciating it must have been.

505
00:51:11,750 --> 00:51:13,590
But I get to be angry, don't I?

506
00:51:15,270 --> 00:51:17,030
You used me

507
00:51:17,790 --> 00:51:22,830
as a bridge to ruin everything in my life!

508
00:51:29,830 --> 00:51:32,190
Do whatever you please.

509
00:51:35,430 --> 00:51:38,390
I hope you're happy getting your revenge.

510
00:51:42,950 --> 00:51:43,750
Oh,

511
00:51:45,430 --> 00:51:47,310
there's one more thing you should know.

512
00:51:48,630 --> 00:51:51,670
Are you completely sure that your mom has really died?

513
00:52:38,990 --> 00:52:39,910
Hello,

514
00:52:40,390 --> 00:52:42,310
I am Arisa Kulnavee,

515
00:52:42,550 --> 00:52:44,670
representing W Empire.

516
00:52:46,070 --> 00:52:48,470
I would like to inform the press

517
00:52:48,670 --> 00:52:50,590
and the public

518
00:52:51,310 --> 00:52:53,710
that the company is not involved

519
00:52:53,870 --> 00:52:57,310
in causing severe injury to the protester

520
00:52:57,750 --> 00:52:59,750
in the past accident.

521
00:53:00,750 --> 00:53:03,030
Is this going to have an internal impact on the company?

522
00:53:03,470 --> 00:53:05,470
I am getting there.

523
00:53:08,070 --> 00:53:10,230
As a result of an internal investigation,

524
00:53:10,350 --> 00:53:12,190
we have found concealment of information

525
00:53:12,910 --> 00:53:16,950
which affects the company's image and credibility.

526
00:53:17,990 --> 00:53:19,790
Therefore, all the board members

527
00:53:19,830 --> 00:53:21,830
decided that Ms. Weiling

528
00:53:22,470 --> 00:53:24,750
be dismissed from her position as the president of the company,

529
00:53:24,790 --> 00:53:26,190
effective immediately.

530
00:53:26,430 --> 00:53:28,230
There is evidence

531
00:53:28,950 --> 00:53:32,070
that connects to someone from her inner circle.

532
00:53:33,190 --> 00:53:37,430
Right now, a charge for attempted murder is being filed under legal proceedings,

533
00:53:37,790 --> 00:53:40,190
which might trace back to the death

534
00:53:40,630 --> 00:53:43,390
of Mr. Thinnakorn Navakul

535
00:53:43,430 --> 00:53:45,310
and Mrs. Saitharn Navakul,

536
00:53:45,310 --> 00:53:46,870
20 years ago.

537
00:53:49,350 --> 00:53:51,470
Should the truth be revealed in line with the evidence,

538
00:53:51,510 --> 00:53:53,430
she will immediately be charged

539
00:53:54,630 --> 00:53:56,150
with murder.

540
00:54:04,070 --> 00:54:05,790
That information is false.

541
00:54:16,990 --> 00:54:18,110
I am still alive.

542
00:54:31,150 --> 00:54:32,430
Mom...

543
00:54:51,510 --> 00:54:53,230
How did you leave me stuck with vengeance?

544
00:54:53,230 --> 00:54:55,310
How could you to that to me?

545
00:54:56,550 --> 00:54:57,950
How ?

546
00:54:58,470 --> 00:55:00,150
I'm ready for the truth.

547
00:55:01,310 --> 00:55:03,510
Weiling and I have been friends since university.

548
00:55:04,670 --> 00:55:06,870
I've been waiting for an explanation for 20 years.

549
00:55:07,230 --> 00:55:09,630
It would mean nothing if I apologized now.

550
00:55:11,870 --> 00:55:15,150
Why haven't you told me that Mom's still alive?

551
00:55:15,670 --> 00:55:16,990
Why would you do this?

552
00:55:17,030 --> 00:55:19,630
Weiling and Saitharn were having an affair!

553
